    особенности основных показателей
    рентгенокардиометрии в юношеском и зрелом
    возрасте</a> // Матер. конгр. ассоциац. морфол. (АГЭ).
    Морфология. -1993.-Т.105. -Вып. 9-10. -С.151-152.</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2">4. <a
    href="http://lib.sportedu.ru/2SimQuery.idc?Author=Судзиловский%20Ф">Судзиловский
    Ф.В.</a>, <a
    href="http://lib.sportedu.ru/2SimQuery.idc?Author=Гайворонский%20И">Гайворонский
    И.В.</a>, <a href="http://lib.sportedu.ru/2SimQuery.idc?Author=Корнев%20М">Корнев
    М.А.</a>, <a href="http://lib.sportedu.ru/2SimQuery.idc?Author=Косоуров%20А">Косоуров
    А.К.</a> <a
    href="http://lib.sportedu.ru/2SimQuery.idc?Title=Рентгеновский%20метод%20и%20его%20современные%20модификации%20в%20научных%20исследованиях%20и%20в%20учебном%20процессе%20по%20анатомии">Рентгеновский
    метод и его современные модификации в научных
    исследованиях и в учебном процессе по анатомии</a>
    // Тез. докл. III конгр. междун. ассоциац. морфол.
    Морфология. - 1996. -Т. 109. -N 2. -С.93.</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</p>
    <b><p ALIGN="CENTER"><a name="Eng"></a><font size="2">TYPICAL ROENTGENOCARDIOMETRY OF THE
    STUDENTS OF THE MAIN LEARNING GROUP OF RHYSICAL EDUCATIONS</font></p>
    </b><p ALIGN="CENTER"><font size="2">V.Sokolov, A.Kondrashev, E.Kharlamov</font></p>
    <p ALIGN="CENTER"><font size="2">Rostov State Medical University,<br>
    Rostov, Russia</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2"><b>Preface.</b> A particular attention at studying the
    constitutional peculiarities of the organism is paid nowadays (Б.А. Никитюк,
    1996) and the typical anatomy of the cardiovascular system in-vestigation, especially
    among people of the youthful and first mature age has a priorital meaning.</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2">Here the meaning of a &quot;ray&quot; methods of
    heart-investigation increases, as they give an opportunity of researching a living human
    (Ф.В. Судзиловский et al., 1996). It’ s known, that the size and form of
    the heart, which characterize its functional capacity, depend on sex, age and somatic type
    (В.В.Соколов et al., 1996). Inspite of this, the concrete constitutional
    peculiarities of the cardio-vascular shadow of the healthy people with the sufficient
    level of moving activity are studied not sufficiently. </font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2"><b>Methods.</b> The chest roentgenograms in straight
    front projection of 1442 healthy students of the Rostov State Medical University of age 17
    - 22 and both sex, who fulfilled the programme of the main learning group of physical
    education successfully and were occupied in sport sections, have been studied. The
    students’ somatic type was determined by Р.Н. Дорохов &amp; В.Г.
    Петрухин (1989) method, which provides an apportionment of the signs of nanosomic,
    microsomic, microme-sosomic, mesosomic, macromesosomic, macrosomic and meghalosomic types
    in gabarital varying level.</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2"><b>The results of the work and discussion of them.</b>
    The aorta diametre, which is the important index of the intracardial haemodynamics, has
    been researched. The right and left parts of this para-metre have been investigated
    separately. The typical peculiarities of the right auricle and left vent-ricle shadows’
    chord and the arcs altitude (the saliense level) of the right auricle and left ventricle
    were determined as the index characterizing the functional capacity of the corresponding
    heart ca-vities. It’s established, that all aforesaid parametres have the sufficiently
    marked sexual dymor-physm.The both sex constitutional differences are expressed by the
    increasing of these indexes’ numbers from nanosomic to meghalosomic type. The typical
    peculiarities are the most noticeable on the left side of the diametrical aorta size.</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2"><b>The conclusions.</b> The studied
    roentgenocardiometrical parametres of the healthy students of the both sex with the
    sufficient physical activity level are different with people of different somatic types in
    the gabarital varying level. This is to be taken into consideration in the
    roentgenological investigation of the heart. </font></p>
